{
  "stem": "9156.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went right on the stage and said a poem.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My sister, Hannah, who is much more shy than I, never said a word.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think I still have that in my memory because you will hear that in the rest of my story.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I never understand all this hate among religions, among the races, and so on.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have to say that right away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But it's a very early memory.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There are other little memories, oddly enough, mostly related to my mother again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There is a woman who passes by and she stands still and says to Mother, oh, I am so grateful to you, Frau Peiper-- P-E-I-P-E-R-- because you helped me to accept my daughter in spite of what happened.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, I was very little then too, but I knew that she had a child out of wedlock.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That impressed me too, that one accepts anybody, and that was Mother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Father was in the army, was sent back pretty early.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I can't tell you the year, because he actually had been-- always, he had angina and very serious.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he was-- I-- today as an adult, I think he was an interesting man.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "As a child, there was a mixture of loving him and being very afraid of him.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Loving him because he was very stimulating to me from the beginning.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He always walked with me around the corner and we discussed, I think, every problems of the world when I was 10 years old.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The house-- and we had-- I say house, the apartment was always filled with books.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he told me that as a youngster, he was part of a socialist.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And he still was a socialist.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he was persecuted in Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
